Covenant Onyebuchi, a young woman, sent some money to Peter Obi, the Labour Party’s nominee for president.
After praying over the money she planned to give to a “humble man,” Onyebuchi, who met Obi in Enugu’s streets, claimed to have met Obi.
“And today, as I learned that Peter Obi is on Urban Radio, God granted my request. I give God praise for hearing my prayers, as I’m about to bless a modest man.”
Obi collected the envelope and promised to call her
